text: This film just confirmed what I suspected would occur from the moment I heard 2049 was being made...that it's a sequel that shouldn't be made.  Rutger Hauer himself called this film soulless, I couldn't agree more.  It does have its moments,  I will say the cinematography/visuals were intriguing, but at the end of the day this film fails to stand on its own IMHO.  The characters were shallow, the script was disjointed, and the sound was unremarkable.  Unfortunately, this franchise will likely continue with sequels ad nauseum (see Alien); until it just can't be watered down any further...what a shame.

text: Blade Runner 2049 is brilliant, it's got the same feel as the original & Harrison Ford was icing on the cake, I love all the twists & turns & I love how it all comes together with the original film, The protagonist is very similar to the architect from the matrix.  At first I though it was going to be just another big budget B rated remake like the Total Recall & Judge Dredd remake but it didn't disappoint. The story & the giant blue haired Joi reminded me of Motoko Kusanagi from the ghost in the shell anime & Misato Katsuragi & the giant Rei Ayanami from Neon Genesis Evangelion (the end of Evangelion) https://youtu.be/mfcbhJz8YA0?t=92  the giant stone head laying on it's side was an obvious nod to the giant head of Rei Ayanami from the end of Evangelion https://youtu.be/mfcbhJz8YA0?t=218 https://youtu.be/W0ONpH3X6NA?t=259  So many films have been inspired by the original 1982 blade runner film, I can never get enough of tech-noir cyberpunk films & anime, they always push your mind out of the box.

text: Ok, so after seeing all of the comments raving about this film, I watched it.  Wow, what a disappointment.  It's the same plot as the first movie, more or less, with the "twist" that instead of hunting down rogue replicants, our Blade Runner is hunting down the child of a replicant.  The bad guy and the good guys have the same motive, so why are they fighting?  Wallace wants replicants that can procreate.  The rogue replicants want to be able to procreate.  Why are they against one another?  Wallace's replicants are supposed to be perfect now.  No running away.  No disobeying.  So why is there even an army of them ready to start YET ANOTHER rebellion.  The movie ends the same as the first one.  Rebellion of replicants about to take place.  Harrison Ford runs off with his family.  The replicant child isn't even a very viable biproduct.  She's fucking bubble girl.  She can't leave her habitat.  If that's what replicant children will turn out to be, they're 100% useless.  Ain't going to the stars with that.  It's visually stunning, but the plot holes are gigantic and the overall story is pointless.  We've seen this movie before.  This is The Force Awakens of Blade Runner movies.  Just a remake of the first.

text: As a person that has been watching films for 30+ years, Blade Runner 2049 was by far the greatest film of the past decade, imo.  Nothing compares to it. The studio produced a masterpiece to a sequel that was a masterpiece.  It hasnt been done this well since Empire Strikes Back.  Now as a hardcore MCU fan and I'm still blown away with what they did with IW / Endgame with all the different properties in a mega superhero event with a compelling storyline and a great movie, Blade Runner 2049 tops that for the simple fact at the quality of a film.  Now when I say quality, it is one of the most well rounded films of all time.  The cinematography is off the charts.  The MUSIC by Hans Zimmer and Benjamin Wallfisch - just WOW.  The JOI soundtrack and MESA is absolutely breath taking and yes I put it right there with Vangelis.  The characters.  The plot.  The story.  The acting.  The direction.  Everything in the film just works so perfectly well.  This is the type of film that will get better and better in time and become a cult classic just like the first one.  I'm not surprised the Transformers crowd didn't run to the theaters to watch this one, its not for everyone, but I feel its exactly for someone like me, someone who thinks deeply on things and not just satisfied with surface level bull shit.     I think the most compelling and amazing thing was how different it was from the original, yet so equally impressive.  It still felt like Blade Runner, just from a different angle.  Every single detail was impressive.  The fact its 30 years later and the world changed is exactly what would happen.  There would be world events like the 'Black Out' that took place inbetween films.  Big world changing event stuff like that happens all the time.  Secondly, the character K / JOE.  Ryan Gosling was the most perfect casting choice ever to this character.  But the fact in the beginning , he was an 'average joe' replicant.  And then the movie makes you think he's a 'chosen one' like every other lame franchise.  At the end, you realize that he still was an average joe.  All of us think we are the chosen ones in our own life story, but at the end of the day, we are just ordinary people just trying to get by in life.  And the best thing we can as humans is to help the people and effect the ppl around us.  All he did was to reunite Deckard with his daughter.  He didnt save the world.  He didnt join TEAM WALLACE or TEAM REBEL REPLICANTS or TEAM LAPD.  He simply just did the right thing.  It was the most emotional character decision ever created on screen.   And the relationship between K and JOI.  Holy shit.  This was the most amazing thing I've ever witnessed.  It was amazing because of the dynamics of it.  And also, you could look at that relationship in so many different ways and come up with your own thoughts and interpretations.  Was it a real relationship ?  Was it loving if it was real ?  Was it all fake and pathetic ?  So many aspects to discuss.  But the relationship from my perspective was just so loving, I long to replicate that relationship in my own life with a partner !!!

text: Just watched this movie and it has to be one of the best sci fi films ever. It‚Äôs a shame some people will miss out because poor reviews.

It was a visual masterpiece. Almost as good as the first one. But... The story was bland. Plot holes. Too many. The pacing destroyed the narrative cohesion of the story. The story itself was poorly concieved. I perceived this movie as a lost oportunity. So much talent! So much effort! The cast was great. The soundtrack amazing! The virtual girfriend concept was endearing. Someone should really try and give this movie a recut. Make it shorter. Make the story itself coherent. Only than it could be called a complete masterpiece. It is, however, a must watch.

text: blade runner 2049 has nothing to do with blade runner.....it is just a empty shell of a joke borrowing the name blade runner.   even as a stand alone movie,it is a complete joke......a pointless meaningless boring story that goes nowhere.......iv seen 1hr 40 mins of it so far.....   1982 bladerunner was a masterpiece set in a  dystopian claustrophobic city ,the imagery was stunning from start to finish,and the creativity of the world design pure genius.........this 2049 was nothing but a brownish blur from start to finish........the minute i saw the beginning that big expanse of brown over some boring large buildings i knew it was going to suck......   blade runner was littered with moments and lines of genius.........blade runner 2049 was one long blurish blob of suckage....the dialogue was mediocre and even when they tried to make the "maker" sound u know.......they failed miserably at it.....   and i dont understand this new "replicant",they couldnt even get the core of the replicant right......replicants werent this hated or feared publicly thing in the original blade runner,like some kind of andriod in issac asimov movie or alien movie......people werent aware what they were......until u are up close with one of them and u sense the psycopathy and the incredibly deadly intelligence and madness.....   and the replicant whose name i dont remember stepping into the library.....hmm where have i seen that scene before?logans run or some old planet of the ape movie from the 70s?so many ripoffs in this movie.......   i dont get all these showered praise.....has the world gone mad or is it a sad state of the world nowadays people cant tell genius from garbage?   more human than human?i dont think the guy who made this movie understood what that means......it doesnt mean robots giving birth to organic beings.....it means the andriods ability to empathise,feel,sorrow,joy,compassion,pain,anguish and experiences better than humans.
